ealand}}\n|'''{{bkw-big|AUS}}'''\n|'''87\u201346'''\n|bgcolor=#efefef colspan=2 rowspan=1| ''One game playoff for<br />the championship''\n|{{bkw-big|NZL}}\n|{{bkw-big|FIJ}}\n|-\n|2009<br />''[[2009 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|Details]]''\n|align=left|{{flagcountry|Australia}}\n|'''{{bkw-big|AUS}}'''\n|'''98\u201348'''\n|'''97\u201357'''\n|bgcolor=#efefef|''Two-legged tie''\n|{{bkw-big|NZL}}\n|bgcolor=#efefef rowspan=4|No third team competed\n|-\n|2011<br />''[[2011 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|Details]]''\n|align=left|{{flagcountry|Australia}}\n|'''{{bkw-big|AUS}}'''\n|'''77\u201364'''\n|'''92\u201373'''\n|'''82\u201357'''\n|{{bkw-big|NZL}}\n|-\n|2013<br />''[[2013 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|Details]]''\n|align=left|{{flagcountry|New Zealand}}\n|'''{{bkw-big|AUS}}'''\n|'''66\u201350'''\n|'''84\u201366'''\n|bgcolor=#efefef|''Two-legged tie''\n|{{bkw-big|NZL}}\n|-\n|2015<br />''[[2015 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|Details]]''\n|align=left|{{flagcountry|Australia}}\n|'''{{bkw-big|AUS}}'''\n|'''61\u201341'''\n|'''80\u201363'''\n|bgcolor=#efefef|''Two-legged tie''\n|{{bkw-big|NZL}}\n|}\n\n===Medal table===\n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = \n | flag_template  = bkw\n | event          = \n | team           = \n | gold_AUS = 15| silver_AUS = 0 | bronze_AUS = 0\n | gold_NZL = 1 | silver_NZL = 15| bronze_NZL = 0\n | gold_SAM = 0 | silver_SAM = 1 | bronze_SAM = 0\n | gold_FIJ = 0 | silver_FIJ = 0 | bronze_FIJ = 1\n | gold_NCL = 0 | silver_NCL = 0 | bronze_NCL = 1\n}}\n\n==Participating nations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%\"\n! width=170|Nation\n! {{flagicon|AUS}}<br />[[1974 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|1974]]!!{{flagicon|NZL}}<br />[[1978 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|1978]]!!{{flagicon|AUS}}<br />[[1982 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|1982]]!!{{flagicon|AUS}}<br />[[1985 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|1985]]!!{{flagicon|NZL}}<br />[[1989 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|1989]]!!{{flagicon|NZL}}<br />[[1993 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|1993]]!!{{flagicon|AUS}}<br />[[1995 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|1995]]!!{{flagicon|NZL}}<br />[[1997 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|1997]]!!{{flagicon|NZL}}<br />[[2001 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|2001]]!!{{flagicon|AUS}}<br />[[2003 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|2003]]!!{{flagicon|NZL}}<br />[[2005 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|2005]]!!{{flagicon|NZL}}<br />[[2007 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|2007]]!!{{flagicon|AUS}}<br />[[2009 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|2009]]!!{{flagicon|AUS}}<br />[[2011 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|2011]]!!{{flagicon|NZL}}<br />[[2013 FIBA Oceania Championship|2013]]!!{{flagicon|AUS}}<br />[[2015 FIBA Oceania Championship for Women|2015]]!!Years\n|-\n|align=left|{{bk|AUS}}\n|bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''|| ||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''|| '''15'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{bk|FIJ}}\n| || || || || || || || || || || ||bgcolor=#cc9966|'''3rd'''|| || || || || '''1'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{bk|NCL}}\n| || || || || || || ||bgcolor=#cc9966|'''3rd'''|| || || || || || || || || '''1'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{bk|NZL}}\n|bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''||bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''|| '''16'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{bk|SAM}}\n| || || || || ||bgcolor=silver|'''2nd'''|| || || || || || || || || || || '''1'''\n|-\n! Total || 2 || 2 || 2 || 2 || 2 || 2 || 2 || 3 || 2 || 2 || 3 || 3 || 3 || 2 || 2 || 2 || \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.fibaoceania.com/|FIBA Oceania official website}}\n\n{{FIBA Oceania Championship for Women}}\n{{International women's basketball}}\n{{Oceanian Championships}}\n\n[[Category:FIBA Oceania Championship for Women| ]]\n[[Category:Women's basketball competitions in Oceania between national teams|    ]]\n[[Category:Oceanian championships]]\n[[Category:Recurring sporting events established in 1974]]\n[[Category:Recurring sporting events disestablished in 2015]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{for|the men's tournament|FIBA Oceania Championship}}\n{{Infobox sports league\n| Formerly       = \n| logo           = \n| pixels         = \n| caption        = \n| sport          = Basketball\n| fame           = \n| motto          = \n| founded        = 1974\n| folded         = 2015\n| replaced       = [[FIBA Women's Asia Cup]]\n| inaugural      = [[FIBA Oceania Championship for Women 1974|1974]]\n| teams          = 2\n| country        = [[FIBA Oceania]] member nations\n| continent      = [[FIBA Oceania]] ([[Oceania]])\n| champion       = {{bkw|AUS}} (15th title)\n| most_champs    = {{bkw|AUS}} (15 titles)\n| qualification  = \n| website        = [http://www.fibaoceania.com/ www.FIBAOceania.com]\n| singles        = \n| ceo            = \n| Director       = \n| TV             = \n| related_comps  = \n| Founder        = \n}}\nThe '''FIBA Oceania Women's Championship''' is the women's [[basketball]] continental championship of [[Oceania]], played biennially under the auspices of the [[F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Basketball]], the basketball [[sport governing body]], and the [[FIBA Oceania|Oceanian zone]] thereof.  The tournament also serves to [[multi-stage tournament|qualify]] teams for participation in the quadrennial [[FIBA World Championship for Women]] and the [[Basketball at the Summer Olympics|Olympic basketball tournament]].\n\nBeginning in 2017, all FIBA continental championships for women will be held on a two-year cycle, and the continental championships will be part of the qualifying process for either the World Cup or Olympics. The 2015 Oceanian Championships were the last Oceanian Championships to ever be held as starting 2017, the tournament will merge with the [[FIBA Asia Championship]] to give way for the '''FIBA Asia-Pacific Championship'''<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.fiba.com/pages/eng/fc/news/presRele/p/newsid/54422/presReleArti.html |title=Central Board gives green light to new format and calendar of competition |publisher=FIBA |date=11 November 2012 |accessdate=31 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Summaries==\nResults highlighted in blue are Olympic qualifiers, those which aren't are World Championship qualifiers.\n\nAs host nation for the 2000 Olympic Games in [[Sydney]], [[Australia women's national basketball team|Australia]] gained automatic qualification to the Olympics. The withdrawal of American Samoa meant that [[New Zealand women's national basketball team|New Zealand]] won the 1999 tournament through default. Consequently, the FIBA Oceania qualifier into the 2000 Sydney Olympics was [[New Zealand women's national basketball team|New Zealand]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fibaoceania.com/fileadmin/user_upload/_temp_/The_Landon_Trophy_-Bckgrnd_Article.pdf |title=The Landon Trophy for competition between Australian and New Zealand |publisher=FIBA |accessdate=7 September 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130520224106/http://www.fibaoceania.com/fileadmin/user_upload/_temp_/The_Landon_Trophy_-Bckgrnd_Article.pdf |archivedate=20 May 2013 }}</ref>\n\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%; width:100%\"\n|-\n!rowspan=2 width=5%|Year\n!rowspan=2 width=4%|Host\n!colspan=5|Qualification series\n!rowspan=2 width=6%|Bronze medallists\n|-\n!width=6%|Gold\n!width=6%|Ga